User module:

Employee Role table:
  1. id
  2. title
  3. description
  4. visual_status
  5. created_at
  6. updated_at
  
User table:
  1. id
  2. name
  3. email
  4. password
  5. phone
  6. empUserId
  7. employee_role_id
  8. visual_status
  9. created_at
  10. updated_at
  
menu table:
  1. id
  2. menu name
  3. visual_status
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
sub menu table:
  1. id
  2. menu_id
  3. sub menu name
  3. visual_status
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
set permission table:
  1. id
  2. permission id
  3. menu_id
  4. submenu_id
  5. slog_url
  6. serial
  7. logo
  8. visual_status
  9. created_at
  10. updated_at

menu_permission table:
  1. id
  2. empUserId
  3. permission_id
  4. created_at
  5. updated_at
  
  

Steps:
  1. Employee Role        -> CRUD
  2. User                 -> CRUD
  3. menu                 -> CRUD
  4. Sub menu             -> CRUD
  
  3. permission           -> CRUD
  4. menu_permission      -> CRUD
 
Menu showing logic:
  1. set empuserid in session after login
  2. Fetch menu_permission table:
        i. match permission_id against empUserId
       ii. show view_slog from permission table & slog for link
      iii. create route same named as slog
